The minister said that the EU was committed to a 20 per cent reduction in greenhouse gas emissions by 2020 compared with 1990 levels, irrespective of the success of the 'post-2012 agreement', and was ready to commit to a reduction of up to 30 per cent if other large developed regions of the world and developing countries were willing to commit themselves to their responsibilities and capabilities.
The EU's new policy on climate change was based on a new approach to climate change, which was adopted by the Council in June.
